Thank you, Nicole. Good afternoon, and thank you for joining us as we review JFrog's Second Quarter 2025 financial results, which were announced following market close today via press release. Leading the call today will be JFrog's CEO and Co-Founder, Shlomi Ben Haim; and Ed Grabscheid, JFrog's CFO.

During this call, we may make statements related to our business that are forward-looking under federal securities laws and made pursuant to the safe harbor provisions of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995, including statements relating to our future financial performance, including our outlook for Q3 and the full year of 2025.
